flowRoot.flowPara: Buffer Overflow occurs when a program or process tries to store more data than it can on a computer. It can be used for malicious reason.
Use Buffer Overflow as a basic attack troop.
DNS also known as Domain Name System is like a phonebook in a network. It allows for easy lookup. Imagine DNS Poison as erasing that name from the phonebook..
DOS (Denial of Service) is a computer network attack that aims to disable a network by creating a ridiculous amount of traffic in an effort to have its target crash.
Use it as a basic attack troop.

SQL Injection is an attack that targets databases by injecting SQL code that alters the original state of the code. Use it to attack enemy troops in a location with a database. It can only attack troops in a location with a Database.

Imagine if we could use Ping to attack another computer (refer to Ping in Utility Troops). Ping of Death is just that! Ping of Death is distorted and made so that the computer it is pinging cannot handle its request and it crashes the computer.
